data.content:
Yes! Use `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>` — it combines the type check and cast, and gives a clearer failure message:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()
{
    var factory = new HandlerFactory();

    var handler = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<EmailHandler>(factory.Create("email"));

    Assert.AreEqual("email", handler.Type);
}
```

The generic overload returns the cast object, so you can keep asserting on it. No manual cast or null check needed.
